'''Abdullah Baqui''' was born and grew up in [[Gopalganj District (Bangladesh)|Gopalganj]] district in Bangladesh. He graduated from [[Dhaka Medical College]] in 1976, and completed his Masters studies in Public Health (MPH) and Doctorate in Public Health (DrPH) from [[Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health]], Baltimore, USA in 1985 and in 1990 respectively. 
Abdullah Baqui is a [[Public Health]] scientist who confirmed effectiveness of simple but effective strategies to reduce preventable [[Infant|newborn]] deaths.<ref>{{cite web|author=Sarah Boseley |url=http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(08)61912-1/fulltext |title=Abdullah Baqui: saving newborn lives in Bangladesh and globally |publisher=The Lancet |date= |accessdate=2012-07-05}}</ref> 
In last 3 decades, Dr. Baqui's research works confirmed: (a) the use of [[zinc]] supplementation during [[diarrhea]] to reduce the severity of [[child mortality]].<ref>Community randomized trial of zinc supplementation started during diarrhoea reduces morbidity and mortality in Bangladeshi children. BMJ. 2002 Nov 9;325(7372):1059.</ref> (b) the effectiveness of trained [[community health worker]]s providing home based health care to reduce [[neonatal mortality]] by one-third.<ref>Lancet. 2008; 371 (9628): 1936â€“44.</ref> and (c) use of [[Hib vaccine|Hib vaccination]] in Bangladesh to reduce the incidence of [[meningitis]] and X-ray documented [[pneumonia]] in children.<ref>Effectiveness of Haemophilus influenzae type B conjugate vaccine on prevention of pneumonia and meningitis in Bangladeshi children: a case-control study. Pediatr Infect Dis J. 2007 Jul;26(7):565-71.</ref> 
Each of these studies has resulted in influencing policy decisions.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}} For example, [http://www.who.int WHO] and [http://www.unicef.org UNICEF] have now recommended the use of zinc as an [[adjuvant therapy]] for diarrheal episode. [https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&q=cache:I5sGdknWm9MJ:www.dghs.gov.bd/index.php%3Foption%3Dcom_docman%26task%3Ddoc_download%26gid%3D14%26Itemid%3D78%26lang%3Den+national+newborn+health+strategy+in+Bangladesh+2009&hl=en&gl=us&pid=bl&srcid=ADGEESiMCACkH2BZq7QRkbG5OLGuaPDhsRkz1U3_TGofc1EB-TwESgmuTbw7V6w3FjvoGKURRlJJEW19SNNN42F2ieDynIOwObZqPHiKal7lyRXCjBvpl0N-XN_G3LW8aDItLUBbFAOz&sig=AHIEtbSBW1qgaQPaXkbfWBhEftijh7lngg National Neonatal Health Strategy in Bangladesh] has been developed in 2009. More recently a  [http://www.unicef.org/health/files/WHO_FCH_CAH_09.02_eng.pdf WHO-UNICEF joint statement] recommends home visits by trained community health worker as a strategy to improve neonatal survival.
Abdullah Baqui became a Professor in the Department of [[International Health]] in Bloomberg School of Public Health in [[Johns Hopkins University]] in 2009.
In May 2012, the [http://www.coregroup.org CORE Group] honored Dr. Baqui with the [http://www.coregroup.org/component/content/article/113 Dory Storms Child Survival Recognition Award].<ref>Dory Storms Child Survival Recognition Award by CORE group is accessible at http://www.coregroup.org/component/content/article/113 .</ref><ref>Media Report published by Gulf-Times:"Bangladeshi origin health scientist awarded in US" accessible at http://www.gulf-times.com/site/topics/article.asp?cu_no=2&item_no=519432&version=1&template_id=44&parent_id=24 .</ref> Prof. Baqui also received 'Recognition Award' from [http://www.bmana.org Bangladesh Medical Association in North America]<ref>Media Report published by Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha (BSS) accessible at http://www1.bssnews.net/newsDetails.php?cat=0&id=264322$date=2012-07-13&dateCurrent=2012-07-17 .</ref><ref>Media Report published by Financial Express accessible at http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/more.php?date=2012-07-14&news_id=136478 .</ref>

